You are troubleshooting a daemon process and have started the daemon manually from thecommand line so that it does not fork into the background. Which key combination can beused to terminate the daemon?
A)  Ctrl+A
B)  Ctrl+B
C)  Ctrl+C
D)  Ctrl+D
C
C. The Ctrl+C key combination terminates, or kills, a process in a scenario such as theone described here. The Ctrl+D option is a valid key combination but is used to delete thecharacter underneath the cursor.
